The Ogun Deputy Governor, Noimat Salako-Oyedele, and the State Head of Service (HoS), Nafiu Aigoro were thrilled with the artistry display at the MKO Abiola Stadium, in a football match organized between the Ministry Team and Parastatals counterpart to commemorate the Public Service Day in the State. In the women’s category, the Ministry’s team defeated their counterparts from parastatals 3-2 in a penalty shootout, after a goalless draw at full time. In the men’s category, the Ministry’s team trashed the parastatals team 2-1, with the Ministry netting its first goal five minutes into the match, while the equalizer came in the 20 minutes into the game. The winning goal scored by the Ministry’s team was scored toward the end of the match through a free-kick.   FG rescinds decision on international basketball withdrawal     WAFU B Under-17 : Ugbade, Michael talk tough ahead of…     Unveiled: Five teen stars tipped to shine at AFN trials   In their separate remarks, the deputy governor, urged the female football team to be more committed to their job, saying it is imperative to something keeping fit, as its part of work exercise. Also, the HoS, Aigoro, admonished the civil servants in the State, to engage in more exercise, so as to be more active intelligently in the course of their job. “When you exercise your body, it will also result or improve your productivity at working place, there must be a time of work and there must be a time of play, that’s why the public service day is set aside yearly, so as to exercise our bodies and keep fit.” he said At the end of the event, medals were awarded to outstanding players.